Diagram 1 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White 1 is a good starting point. If you can find this move, there is no way you will get this problem wrong.
\par
\par Black 2 is unavoidable. Black has to avoid the snapback.
\par
\par White connects at 3 and black is dead. Now even if black connects at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , it does no good.
\par }
