Diagram 2 (Snapback)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par This is a variant of the correct answer.
\par As mentioned before, in response to white \'a1\'e2 if black tries to resist and cuts with 1, white creates a snapback at 2.
\par
\par In this case, black is also dead.
\par
\par As soon as black suffers the blow of white \'a1\'e2, black has no way to live.
\par }
